Program: The History Hour
Title: Drama in the British parliament
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqn1
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 1 Apr 2019
Prime Minister Jim Callaghan's desperate attempts to survive a no-confidence motion in 1979, the record-breaking 20-day balloon flight around the world; plus the Nazi past of Kurt Waldheim, mindfulness and the first home pregnancy test. Picture: James Callaghan outside 10 Downing Street (Fox Photos/Getty) Show less